stats UI

  { Fl_Window* o = statsdbox = new Fl_Window(520, 165, msg_stats_title);

stats dbox has close, all-desktops, minimise, isn't resizeable and currently isn't big enough !!
 Minimise seems a little pointless, as it doesn't update until you close and reopen it. So it
 probably should be modal.

-------------

find UI

  { Fl_Window* o = findbox = new Fl_Window(500, 65, msg_find_title);
    o->labeltype(FL_NO_LABEL);
    o->hotspot( find_ok, 0);

find dbox has close, all-desktops, minimise, isn't resizeable and currently isn't big enough !!

It probably ought to be modal and not have minimise

-------------

completions UI

  { Fl_Window* o = completionswin = new Fl_Window( 400, 500, msg_completions_title );
    o->labeltype(FL_NO_LABEL);

completions window has close, all-desktops, minimise, maximise, vertical scrollbar and is resizable,
but really ought to be a fixed width (we've calculated column widths to fit the data we are going
to display, so resizing the window horizontally makes very little sense).

Having a minimise button is a bit off, as you can minimise it and forget it's there, which
has side effects if you want to open a new one (the old one gets closed, but the new one
kinda remembers where it was...)

-------------

info UI

  Fl_Window* w = info_panel = new Fl_Window( 520, 210, msg_info_title );
  w->labeltype(FL_NORMAL_LABEL);
  w->set_non_modal();

info window has close, all-desktops, minimise, isn't resizeable and currently isn't big enough
 if you click on the Â© button. Also, when you do that, the OK button obscures some of
 the text. Altogether rather shambolic :-(

info UI shouldn't have a minimise button, and should probably be modal.
OK, removing w->set_non_modal(); didn't help and adding
w->set_modal(); left infoUI with a minimise icon still, which when clicked,
resulted in the window disappearing, with nothing on the task bar, but the
remaining mainUI windows totally unresponsive

