-------------

notes UI

  window = new Fl_Window(720, 305, notes_title);
  window->resizable(input);

notes window has close, all-desktops, minimise, maximise and is resizeable, but needs,
 and doesn't have, scrollbars. It has what looks like a menu bar (and indeed, looking
 at the code, that's what it is), but which really acts like a load of buttons.
 As such, the buttons should be made to look like buttons, and should be at the
 bottom of the window, not the top.

OK, so the text is displayed in an   input = new Fl_Multiline_Input(0, 55, 720, 250);
can we put that inside an Fl_Scroll ?

Alternative approach is to use an Fl_Text_Display - this seems to have worked,
using fix0007, except that a Text_Display expects us to have callbacks for all
the editing things, so perhaps we now need to change it to an Fl_Text_Editor
widget instead... - remarkable, we changed just four lines and that worked :-)

-------------

A number of the windows uses the current tree filename in the title, but
are not really big enough - indiUI, famUI, ...

notes UI has the filename in the window title, but not the name of the FAM or
INDI (or event) on which it is raised, which makes it hard to identify in
the task bar if you have a load open (and maybe minimised)

findUI and completions UI have no indication in the window title of the
filename.

main UI title includes filename and current INDI name, but perhaps
in the wrong order, but that's debatable. Which bit of info is more
important if you have a small bit of tree displayed so there isn't
room for both ?
